caption: Owners and staff go WAYYY beyond the call of duty to help the customer and bend over backwards to make them happy. Pleasant eating experience. Food is really Lovely, special. Very happy experience.

Looked like the best Thai joint in Park Slope on our recent visit from Ridgewood and our impression was on point. The flavors were authentically Thai and the food was delicious. The spare ribs were seasoned so well, the rainbow salad was a fun healthy treat, and their pad thai was seasoned so well it is miles ahead of the typical US fair. I'm already looking forward to my next trip to Park Slope so I can find a reason to come back here!
Really enjoyed my visit. Though the interior was closed, the vibe is very unique.  My meal was also fantastic and service was very speedy.  Would return.
Delicious food. Some of the best thai food in bk. I was there a couple nights ago when it was rainy, sat outside, service was a little slow probably due to all the takeout orders.
Get the whole fish deep fried...its amazing
Really authentic thai food. Brings back memories of travel there... So delicious!!
Drunken noodles!
Delicious flavors! Everything I've eaten here has clearly been prepared with care and lots of fresh ingredients. Recommended!

Yummy Thai food- far superior than many others in the neighborhood. Pad Thai was a bit on the sweeter side but great flavor. Massaman curry is on point - really tender short ribs and rich spices. Amazing service!

This has been my favorite Thai spot since it’s opened; a real godsend as high quality and farm-to-table food is not so typical for Thai restaurants.  We usually order take out but this time decided to go sit at their street-seating and I have to say I was shocked and disappointed by what I experienced.  First, we were told to grab an empty table which was clearly not clean nor sanitized (we asked for it to be cleaned and it was).  We were then handed plastic menus that were clearly not cleaned in a long time, let alone since the previous customer (they were stained with food and finger prints).  Those things alone freaked me out enough, but then various other small things deepened the disappointment - service was slow; cutlery wasn’t provided for all four of us and when we asked, we got some plastic utensils but were still short on what we needed; one of our noodle dishes was poorly done with way too much sauce and salt; and in general the outside area didn’t look to be tended to very well with some rubbish lying around beneath the tables.  It seems to me like they are too busy to handle the demand and they are slipping.  We’re all trying to be more patient with our neighborhood restaurants during these unprecedented times, but there is no room to drop the ball on hygiene and sanitation during a pandemic.  Will continue to give them a chance because I love the food but I will be more cautious going forward.

Ate here on Sunday night after everything was closed in the area. We were seated even though it was fifteen minutes prior to closing. The staff is warm and corteous, encouraged us to take our time as we sat outside. Ordered the calamari and spicy panang curry with shrimp and green curry with chicken. The portions were generous and we had no room for desert. Authentic flavors with real basil. It's a good place for Thai.

Just tried delivery for the first time last night and it was awesome! The menu is a lot more exciting than my go to Thai takeout place and all the food had complex flavors and plenty of heat. Really enjoyed the khao soi and the shrimp with Brussels sprouts. Looking forward to checking out their garden.

I love Thai food and Jintana serves delicious authentic Thai! My favorite dish is the Pad See yew and the Panang curry! I’m also obsess with their Thai Ice Coffee! I’ve only ordered out and yet to dine at their place but they also have good customer service!
The meals and service were ahead of my expectations. I really enjoyed the atmosphere of this restaurant. First-rate spot to take my family out for dinner.
Very good

caption: Ordered from here the other day. DAMMMN it’s some good Thai food. They don’t skimp out on the veggies so I am sold!

This is some of the best thai food I've ever had in New York City. Ever since I discovered it, I've ordered delivery nearly nightly, and it has been a godsend during this whole quarantine situation. I can't wait until this is over so I can eat there in person.

Very well organised and accessible restaurant. They serve generous meals and for affordable rates. I loved the food a lot and the staff members were super amiable and informative. Will definitely recommend this place.
Thai curry and Momo was great Loved the ambiance

Looked for a new Thai place for lunch. The prior reviews are very much true: very fresh flavors, good portions, extremely courteous service. The lunch special is a great way to try this place. The panang Curry is a tad too spicy ( please let customers know the spice levels). The pad see ew was perfect!  Otherwise a very pleasing meal. Hopefully we will be back.
The food was really delicious. Helpful staff.
Definitely a place worth stopping over, the food is fantastic and well prepared, the prices are fair and it is regularly well organized there. 5 stars.
Good food, a quite place...
Lazy delivery driver refused to come up in the elevator.  They called then hung up on us.
Spaghetti kee Mao is great!
Food was pretty standard Thai, nothing very special. And they rushed us through our meal, taking my food before I was finished.
Excellent food, nice portions
Delicious Thai food (just the right amount of heat!) and friendly service.
Great food and really nice atmosphere.  We were there while a huge party was there and they were able to handle everyone.
Really loved this fresh flavorful lunch special!

This is the best Thai food on 7th Ave and conveniently located near the F/G subway at 7th Ave & 9th street. I have tried several dishes and all of them used authentic and flavorful ingredients.   The Gai Yang (grilled chicken) and Panang curry ordered as Thai spicy (extra spicy) are both excellent. They have a small but  nicely decorated area for dining in and they offer take out.
Everything in the menu was very  delicious 😋! The service was very friendly & sweet by the girl named Pena! I’m so exited to go back to this place again❤️
Very good Thai food. Highly recommend!

First time come here since friend want to have some thai food. Found this on yelp some decided on this place . The service is great the good we sat all the way in the front so didnt get to see the whole place. But the food is delicious only 1 thing was the sticky rice was a bit undercook but over all everything is good. Would I come back I would say yes.
It is cute inside, service was good as was food.
Certainly the most consistent and authentically Thai food I've had in Brooklyn. Not 100% Thai but a treat all the same, and the service was excellent.
Delicious green curry.  Consistently good, well priced, quick service.  A go to.
Not your usual Thai place. Great food, although somehow everyone around me had more interesting dishes than I ordered. Will go back to try more stuff.
Best Thai in NYC.
Much better than your average Thai restaurant. Tastes very fresh and high-quality. Tried the Pad Thai & Panang Curry, along with soup & spring roll, everything was delicious!
This place is worth a try. They have big portions for affordable rates. Constantly well kept and with fantastic vibes. Highly recommended.
I’m not well versed in Thai but I can tell this is the real deal. Soooo good
Best Thai around.  Have a kids menu too!
Best Thai food I’ve ever eaten. Vegetables and chicken cooked to perfection. I recommend to make a reservation, because this place is frequently visited.

I may not be the best person to do a review on Thai food however after just getting back from Thailand and having a fantastic time through this place is mediocre at best the portions were very small and the flavor of the food was pretty much without taste Thailand is known as the land of smiles there’s that one smile among the lady sure waiting on me sorry I was looking forward to this restaurant very much however I was very disappointed

Friendly servers- all of them checked in on us and helped each other throughout the night. Tried the pad see ew, pad thai, and massaman short ribs! Big portions and delicious. Looking forward to going back :)
Super authentic. Fantastic addition to the neighborhood!
very nice and good lunch deal. The only complaint (I should have said it at the time) was that there was a slightly burnt taste off my noodles

Best Thai food I’ve had in a very long time. Everything is feels quite authentic and is simply deliciousness. Staff was courteous, professional and quick. I especially loved the green curry dish and the presentation of everything really adds to the charm. Very clean open kitchen also made me happy. Outdoor seating a major plus. I’ve been 4 times since opening and they are brand new. Give them a shot.
Food is flat out amazing. Fresh, clean, full of flavor and beautifully presented. Best Thai I’ve had in the neighborhood.
Food was Excellent,ordered Calamari  and Chefs Steak was Delicious. Chef from Thai farm kitchen Good Service

Tonight was my third trip to this gem. The food is so delicious and fresh tasting. I'm slowly working my way through the menu. The Tom Kha Gai (chicken coconut soup) was super savory with the lightest coconut flavor. I got the Pad Krapow with ground pork and it was excellent. I would have preferred it a tad spicier (I asked for Thai spicy) but the flavor was excellent.
Great food. authentic taste from what I know.

The service here is a hit or miss. The matre'd was delightful and courteous. The servers are not as on point. We were a party of 5 and were seated in the back. They gave us 4 settings and when they brought over the water one glass was half filled. Then we ordered drinks on the side our server brought 3 of the 5 drinks and then she blanked out. We had to asked for it.  The food was just ok. I've had better at other restaurants. Presentation wise the dishes looked great. Beware of the papaya salad. When they took our order they asked how spicy we would like it and we ordered mild. If that was the mild I would not order spicy from this place. I eat spicy foods all the time and that made me sweat. The rest of the party couldn't eat it.

Amazing authentic delicious Thai food, who could ask for anything more?!? Luckily for me I stumbled onto this place on their first day and I'm so grateful for it, it means I could take the journey with them.  I've been there 3x's since they opened and I won't slow down until I try every dish! So far they have not missed a beat. Green curry chicken, Basil Chicken and Whole fried Branzino were all absolutely perfect, so delicious I forgot to take pics! This place will soon become impossible to get a table but hopefully they'll remember their original customers!

Food was mostly tasty (though some dishes were skimpy on key ingredients, or quite small), but staff needs to tighten up. Hearing them regroup and complain about other customers several times through the meal comes off as unprofessional. It really got in the way of what should have been a nice meal with my family.
Really great food and friendly service. Rich ingredients, delicious soup , the Panang curry was very tasty. Happy to have them in the neighborhood.
